modules.description: This module tracks POSIX time with picosecond precision using a paravirtualized clock interface, providing the current time as a day count and picoseconds since the Unix epoch. It supports querying the local time zone offset in seconds and the clock's period in days and picoseconds, if available. Use this to implement time-sensitive networking protocols or timestamping mechanisms that require high-resolution timing and UTC conversions.

Provides access to a monotonic clock with nanosecond precision, returning time elapsed since an arbitrary starting point. Works with 64-bit integers to represent time values in nanoseconds, suitable for profiling and timing measurements. Useful for tracking durations and synchronizing time-sensitive operations in low-level systems code.
